## Scenario Design

FORMAT-09 introduces three axes.

### Axis A — Metadata regime

Scenarios must explicitly control metadata survivability.

Values:

metadata_intact
metadata_destroyed
metadata_partial
metadata_conflicting

Definitions:

metadata_intact
    No direct corruption of metadata layers.

metadata_destroyed
    All manifest/path metadata regions destroyed.

metadata_partial
    One or more metadata fragments survive.

metadata_conflicting
    Multiple inconsistent metadata fragments exist.

---

### Axis B — Metadata damage targets

Targets include:

index
manifest
path_checkpoint
tail_metadata
multiple_metadata_layers

Corruption operations:

delete
truncate
bitflip
overwrite

---

### Axis C — Payload topology damage

Payload damage regimes:

none
single_block_delete
sparse_delete
cluster_delete
block_reorder
duplicate_block_insert

---

## Scenario Matrix

Each metadata regime must combine with multiple
payload topologies.

Minimum recommended families:

1. Metadata-only loss

   index destroyed
   manifest destroyed
   path checkpoints destroyed
   index + manifest destroyed

2. Metadata survives, payload damaged

   payload sparse deletion
   payload clustered deletion

3. Partial metadata survival

   single manifest fragment survives
   single path checkpoint survives

4. Conflicting metadata remnants

   two manifest fragments disagree
   duplicate path checkpoints conflict

Total scenarios should be between 24 and 40.

---

## Metrics Collected

For each scenario record:

strategy
scenario_id
metadata_regime
metadata_target
payload_damage

Recovery metrics:

named_recovery
anonymous_full_recovery
partial_ordered_recovery
partial_unordered_recovery
orphan_evidence

Metadata survival metrics:

manifest_checkpoint_survival_count
path_checkpoint_survival_count
verified_metadata_node_count

Additional metric:

metadata_recovery_gain

Definition:

metadata_recovery_gain measures the change in recovery class
when metadata fragments survive versus when they do not.

